# Neighbo — Project Overview

## What Is This App?
Neighbo is a **values-based restaurant and business discovery platform** (mobile-first PWA). Users filter local restaurants by values (LGBTQ+ friendly, sustainable, Black-owned, union labor, etc.) and see tiered certification badges (Tier 1: self-attested, Tier 2: community-vetted, Tier 3: moderator-verified). Businesses pay for advertising and analytics; consumers always use the platform free.

**Target market:** Twin Cities (Minneapolis/St. Paul), Minnesota — pilot market.
**Full business context:** @docs/business-context.md

## Monorepo Structure
```
apps/web/       # React 19 + TanStack Router + Capacitor (iOS/Android)
apps/api/       # Hono.js REST/RPC API (port 3001)
packages/shared/ # Shared Zod schemas + TypeScript types
```

## Key Commands
```bash
bun run dev          # All workspaces
bun run dev:web      # Web only (port 5173)
bun run dev:api      # API only (port 3001, hot-reload)
bun run typecheck    # Type-check all workspaces
bunx biome check --write .  # Auto-fix lint + format
```

